Following the resignation of the indicted and suspended Chief Justice of Nigeria, Onnoghen after the Nigerian Judicial Council (NJC) advised the President to retire him because the EFCC has proven beyond reasonable doubt, with incontrovertible evidence, that Onnoghen is guilty of misdemeanor and corruption, Nigerians have taken to social media to share their thoughts on the sudden climax to the protracted case. While some feel he should be further prosecuted, others feel that the acceptance of his resignation with full entitlements is a sign of a ‘dirty job.’